.TH "ide_hw_configure" 9 "ide_hw_configure" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ide_hw_configure \- configure a struct ide_hw instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ide_hw_configure
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct ide_port_info *d "  ","
.BI "unsigned int port "  ","
.BI "struct ide_hw *hw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device holding interface
.IP "d" 12
IDE port info
.IP "port" 12
port number
.IP "hw" 12
struct ide_hw instance corresponding to this port

Perform the initial set up for the hardware interface structure. This
is done per interface port rather than per PCI device. There may be
more than one port per device.

Returns zero on success or an error code.
